,Recommended,253030,11283592,"Posted: 16 July, 2014",all,JJRcop,"Race The Sun is a fast-paced racing game. You contol a solar powered speeder, attempting to stay in the sun so you can keep blazing through a minimalistic world, gaining points over time as long as you stay alive. Unfortunately, the sun is still setting even as you are shooting above the ground, so you have to pick up yellow boost powerups that temporarily cause your speeder to goREALLYfast, so fast that the sun raises in the sky as you are going faster than it is setting. There are blue triangles scattered across the level that give you points, and getting five of them multiplies the passive point gains you get.The level you play in are separated into regions, each region giving you harder and harder obstacles. The level is procedurally generated every 24 hours, being consistent for all players for that day.Hitting a wall kills you, and the run is over. If the sun sets, or you simply sit in the shadows too long, you will lose power. This isn't an instant loss, but without power the craft starts slowing down, eventually coming to a stop if you can't get sunlight fast enough. When you do come to a stop, the run is over and you have to try again.There are little tasks that the game gives you to do. There are easy, medium, and hard tasks. Completing the tasks will give you experience that goes towards leveling up, leveling up unlocks more features. Easy tasks give one experience point, medium tasks give two, and hard tasks give three. Please note: the multiplier and boost are only available after you unlock them, but it's only level 2-3, which is simple to get. There are also a ton of more fun features you unlock as you level up, like power ups, and ship decals.You can't beat the game, you just go as long as you can, getting as many points as you can. There are leaderboards that reset each day as the level is regenerated, so you can compete with your friends, and the world.Overall, I thoroughly enjoy this game, and I hope you get it.Unless you don't like these kind of games, I completely understand."
