,Recommended,253030,8010022,"Posted: 11 December, 2013",all,Zero,"I'm absolutely loving this game.It starts as your standard high speed ""dodge absolutely everything"" style game (which to be perfectly honest is good enough for me to begin with. I love games like that), but quickly upgrades, achievements, accelerated movement, compounding level complexity, and ever approaching impending doom (the setting sun) escalate and elevate things beyond the competition.The game runs, as expected, incredibly smoothly on my i7 980x and GTX 680 at maximum settings and resolution. I suspect more modest systems would run it quite happily as well.The graphics are a bit retro, but very clean and adequately appealing. Most importantly, it effectively conveys a sense of speed.If you've never played any games in this genre (or happen to be a fan of them), Race The Sun is most akin to the Android game ""SpeedX 3D"", or the flash games ""3D Missile Game"" and its newer sibling ""Accelerator"".Links to the mentioned games:https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.gamelion.speedx3dhttp://missile-game.bwhmather.com/http://www.newgrounds.com/portal/view/627313Bottom line: If you like ""infinite run"" games, RTS is a winner even at full price, and a steal with the current Steam discount."
