,Recommended,253030,9827164,"Posted: 15 April, 2014",all,Riktar,"I have played this game for a few hours over a coupe of days and it is awesome. The controls are simple (so far it's left, right and when you have a jump spacebar / A (on controller)) They feel about right once you get use to the senstivity.The difficulty increases with each region you get through - within the first hour of play I went from barely passing region 1 to perfect region 1 and 2 and making it through 3 into region 4. If that wasnt' crazy enough I unlocked Armageddon mode and it quickly humbled me.The world resets every 24 hours so there are new challenges every day with the new map to explore.I've played with a controller and keyboard - both feel very good - I prefer controller myself though.I had a few issues getting it to start - but the support from the developement team was very quick and thorough - my issues are resolved and the game runs very smooth...now I just need time to practice so I can go for top scores."
,Recommended,253030,9633738,"Posted: 26 March, 2014",all,L1qu1d,"This game is easy to recommend, especially for those that don't have much time to invest in a game and just want something easy and fun to play.Now the game is simple, what I mean by this is that the controls are straight forward and so is the main objective...race to the sun. The actual gameplay is a different factor, it can be VERY challenging in terms of actually making it far at least for me.The obstacles you'll be facing start off very easy but then turn extremely challenging and a lot of the times very cheap. Especially playing through it the first time, you will not be able to predict how to dodge the objects which means this game forces you into death until you learn the patterns. This was a little bit of a let down only because I was looking forward to reaction time playing a role here not just guess and check.To put it simple, you will die, you will die a lot. You will also try to avoid dieing but most of the time you'll have to do that in your second try.Does this put a damper on the game play? To an extend yes, but it doesn't hurt the over all game. The game looks great, plays great and frankly has some awesome moments that remind me of Journey. I'm sure there will be quite a few people that will enjoy playing this game on and off between classes, work or on lazy days.8.0/10 if you pick up during a sale and 7.5/10 if you purchase it at full price. Although the game is fun either way I feel that it didn't quite live up to the initial hype, but we did get a solid product!"
