76561197970038516,Recommended,253030,8356310,"Posted: 27 December, 2013",all,Ellis Island Book Club Militia,"This game is amazingly fun and incredibly addictive. Although this game is technically a racing game, it barely fits the criteria for being in the genre. I've typically disliked most racing games, but this one is super fun. This game is very addictive and will make you tell yourself ""just one more time, then I'm done"" more times than you can count. In this game, you are, literally, racing the sun - when you stay in the dark for too long, you die. As the sun goes down, the shadows cast by the various objects become your worst enemy, making things increasingly difficult to survive. The developers implemented a leveling system, giving you access to several powerups and decals for your plane for completing various objectives - namely things like ""score X amount of points"" or ""don't turn left through 1 region"". Although basic, the leveling system adds a fun incentive for replayability. This game has been well-designed and I recommend buying it, even at full price. If you manage to find it on sale, then it is a steal."
76561198292631324,Recommended,253030,28241807,"Posted: 7 December, 2016",all,76561198292631324,"PLAY IN A FIRST PERSON VIEW MODE!Race the Sunis a game about collecting seagulls poop and unlocking colourful worlds, next to magical powers. It is a futuristic racing game, a good one. It is fast, it is furious, it is abstract, there is a sense of humour in it, there are even philosophical tidbits. But first of all, there are advancement levels to be gained through solving challenges, as well as additional achievements to be reached for, with plenty of emotions to be had along the way. Obtaining further levels opens road to the technological implementations and features, which empower the experience and final score. Eventually new modes of play are enabled.The game looks conceptually coordinated with the solar craft riding against the setting sun, the death-timer. The action is placed within an Egyptian-like minimalistic desert environment. Nevertheless, there are also beautiful side-worlds to be discovered - milk and honey, if you are persistent and lucky. Speaking of the basic map, a new scheme is generated each day, with a new leaderboard to be settled for it.Race the Sunis perhaps a perfect speedrunning game in the futuristic abstract tone with minimalist design style. 8/10 wHATs grade. Definitely recommendable to those who want to feel the vibe of screen image shaking under the impact of acceleration."
