76561197998492220,Recommended,253030,12315358,"Posted: 1 October, 2014",all,Flutterrock,"Note: Summary at the bottom of the review.How can a game that is so simple be so addictive and feel so right? If you know, you could likely make a lot of money out of that knowledge!-Regardless, this is a very simple game. You dodge the obstacles and gather the power-ups and ""coins"" (glowy triangle pyramids in this case). Sooner or later you either run out of solar energy, or, more likely, you hit an obstacle. You'll be annoyed, you'll likely swear some...and 30 seconds later, you will be playing again. Bit by bit you learn the track, and your score creeps upwards, and the next day, there is a new track. You do it all over again...and you love ever moment of it.Pro:*Simple, anyone can play this.*Exellent pick-up-and-play-for-5-minutes gameplay.*Superb ""goals"" that is attainable for anyone over time (only turn right for one zone, etc).*Gets your heart pumping as you zoom past obstacles, and frequently, into them.Con:*As usual with this genre, you are only travelling in one direction, and cannot turn around. I realise listing this as a ""con"" is subjective, ignore this point if you do not agree!*Likely to waste a LOT of your time, this game is addictive, you've been warned!Summary:An ""endless runner"" that is very simple, yet both stylish and fun. If you like endless runners, this might be what you have been looking for. Even if you do not like endless runners (I don't), this is worth a try simply for the excitement of zooming past huge cubes and falling blocks that tries to crush you!7/10 -Recommended!For more recomendations and reviews:http://steamcommunity.com/groups/strandedkerbonaut#curation"
