,Recommended,253030,15804701,"Posted: 12 May, 2015",all,Dr∞gonslayer,"This game is a masterpiece. Simple to the point of minimalist, but polished to a mirror sheen. There's a kind of zen-like peace in the pattern of flying, crashing, flying slightly farther, and feeling yourself slowly but steadily improving. The challenge system (by which you gain points towards leveling up, which in turn unlocks new upgrades and decals) is also simple, but incredibly addictive, and these challenges are creatively thought out, and will force you to approach the game in all kinds of new ways. It keeps the game from getting boring, and is always a great incentive to come back.I only wish the game had a bit more to offer beyond level 25. I have five hours on record here, and it was enough to let me reach the maximum level. There are two alternate game modes to unlock, both of which are quite unique and interesting, but it was the challenges that really kept me coming back, and it was frustrating seeing them disappear upon reaching the max level, even though there were clearly several left that I hadn't been able to finish.All in all, an absolutely worthwhile ten bucks, and a wonderful diversion that rewards patience, tenacity and skill."
