,Recommended,253030,9716554,"Posted: 3 April, 2014",all,Freds Undead,"Race the Sun is a behind the back endless runner (Flyer?) that allows for little room of error. Often times onehit is all it takes to down you. That being said, as you progress in attempts you unlock new abilities; which include: boost, revive, jump, multiplier, etc... These abilities are custumizable and are unlocked in the way of challanges, which at first seem very difficult, but continued play will see them unlock. As for the achivements, some are glitched and others are just daunting, this is one of those games that each achivement earned is a trimuph. The game supports steam workshop which generally, provided reskined backgrounds, which are often a nice change from the usual background. Once you reach level 10 you unlock armeggedon mode which throws all the higher region difficulty at you up front, I recommend the game for those who like games in the vein of Temple Run or other other endless runners."
