76561198307167376,Recommended,253030,28753429,"Posted: 28 December, 2016",all,harry.washello,"Simple extremely well executed 3D game5/10★★★★★☆☆☆☆☆GameplayRace The Sunis a successful reinvention of a 3D arcade genre. Going ahead avoiding obstacles seems too little for 2016, but it is not, if it's done right. The game is about the sense of freedom flight gives, about swiftness in an open space. In spite of the simple premise, the competent execution makesRace The Sunsurprisigly plaesent and addictive experience.The games offers additions to a ship. The world changes,Steam Workshopis there and the game has a level editor; I do not usually feel like using level editors, but I will definitely play with this one.PresentationGraphicsare elegant-type simple, crisp and clear. This fits the game's theme perfectly, finds the perfect balance between aesthetics and simplicty. Rendered on a big screen in high resolution offers unprecedented level of sense of speed and freedom.Audio... is disappoiting. Maybe it was supposed to have the elegancy and simplicity of the graphics, but it is just basic, lacking the overall game's refinement. Music commits the same sin - it is blunt and ill-chosen -c'mon guys - we are flying a solar bird toward the setting Sun; can't you come up with something more subtle?Summing upSuccessful reinvention of 3D arcade genre.positivepleasent and addictive gameplaydistinctive captivating 3D graphicswell-paced game flow, fast level restartwell-set difficulty levelchanging world - great replayabilityeasy level editor adding to replayabilitybest credits every - credits within the gameSteam Workshopwell pricednegativeuninspired audiomusic not living up to the game's styleLooks right, feels right. Highly recommended."
