,Not Recommended,253030,29869417,Posted: 12 February,all,Iamfishyfishy,"I got this game a few years ago and I haven't even touched it since. Rarely an update would show up, and even then it did very minimal.The gameplay itself is rather simplistic: You manouver a small air-craft through levels endlessly until you either crash or the sun sets, hence the name ""Race the Sun"". The game is easy at first, turn right, turn left, maybe jump. Pretty fun for the first say what, 10 minutes, 30 minutes, multiple hours, depending on who you are. But that's the entire game, you repeatedly play the same level with a little extra thrown in or taken out every day, yes it changes every day, and avoid obstacles while making it as far as possible. Shadows will slow you down. That's the full extent of the game, fairly shallow to say the least. There are these so-to-speak, World Portals, which will take you to a user-made level. Since there's no telling if they've made it literally impossible, that could potentially be fatal and cause you to start over again. There's no checkpoints, no saving, nothing. You start again.There's an ""Ultra-hard world"" called Apocaplypse, which supposedly makes you go faster than before and is significantly more difficult. Moving on from that, there's the paid DLC which you can purchase for a measly single level, which has almost zero challenge unless you're that uncoordinated. All you do is endlessly fly until you deliberately crash or exit the game. This is a good level to play if you're looking for a relaxing time and you can mute the in-game music so you can listen to your own while you do that, typically good if you have a controller and somewhere to lay back and chill out.In general, the game lacks simple things like more diverse levels or more music, just things that make it fun. As a player, I don't see why we should have to make our own levels to add anything interesting to the game, we should be able to choose from a few levels at the least. Yes, it's great you can make your own levels, but players shouldn't have to be doing majority of the work for developers. If you don't mind a rage-game in disguise and are willing to pay $10USD, knock yourself out. Otherwise, steer clear, this game just reeks of cash-grab."
