,Recommended,253030,34788735,Posted: 6 September,all,Z/-\|\|[)O1[),"WARNING!: EXTREMELY ADDICTIVE GAMEPLAY!That is what it should say on the store page for Race the Sun.From the small amount of this game that I have played so far (as of September 2017) I think this game is amazing. It is, as stated above, extremely addictive. A lot of the levels (especially as you progress to Apocalypse mode) are VERY difficult, and at times, controller-throwing-worthy frustrating. However, It is extremely replayable, and, with patience you will eventually start progressing faster. Oh, and did I mention that the levels CHANGE COMPLETELY every 24 hours, AND it has very nice soundtrack that suits the game PERFECTLY. It also has decent compatibility with LinuxThe one complaint that I have about the game is that I have a lot of difficulty setting up my Steam Controller to work with it. However, that may just be user error on my part (wouldn't surprise me). But that (and limited spare time) is the only reason I don't have more time on this game.I would highly recommend picking up this game at some point.9.99/10 ""Very Noice."""
